eNCA's Nkosazana Dambuza has more. #DStv403 #eNCA JOHANNESBURG - Smoking kills at least eight million people every year. World No Tobacco Day aims to reduce diseases and deaths caused by the consumption of tobacco. More and more smokers are quitting the addictive habit amid the COVID-19 pandemic. A year ago, many smokers couldn't buy cigarettes due to the sales ban. Some quit. But others looked to the illegal market to feed their cravings. Smoking kills, but that's not the reason why some dropped their cigarettes during the lockdown. Watch the full story in the video above.